cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for extracting abbreviations and their corresponding long-form expansions from unstructured text. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper also involves techniques for scoring expansion candidates, which falls under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Learning (cs.LG). The use of machine learning algorithms also suggests that it could belong to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
